# Business Logic & API Conventions

Follow the API contract and enforce domain rules in forms.

## Rules

1. **Soft delete.** When the backend implements soft delete via DELETE, use `api.delete()` not `api.put()`. Follow the API contract.
2. **Child destination type.** When creating a child destination (parent selected), disable the "Country" type option. Country must be top-level only.

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD: PUT for soft delete
await api.put(`/catalog/locations/${id}`, { deleted: true });

// GOOD: DELETE for soft delete
await api.delete(`/catalog/locations/${destinationId}`);
```

```typescript
// GOOD: Disable Country when parent is locked (creating child)
const isDisabled = isParentLocked && dtype === "Country";
<ToggleGroupItem value="Country" disabled={isDisabled} />
```

**Reference:** `features/delete-destination/api/useDeleteDestination.ts`, `features/create-destination/ui/CreateDestinationModal.tsx`
